To determine how long it would take Tom to dry 7 pairs of socks, we need to first find out how long it took for the 10 pairs of socks to dry. Since the 10 pairs of socks dried in 10 hours when the weather conditions were the same, it will also take 10 hours for the 7 pairs of socks to dry under these same conditions.

So, it will take Tom 10 hours to dry seven pairs of socks presuming the same weather conditions.
